<TITLE> Russia's Putin backs Abbas unity drive </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MOSCOW, July 31 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Russian President Vladimir Putin endorsed Mahmoud Abbas on Tuesday as legitimate leader of the Palestinian people and backed his efforts to end an internal rift in the Palestinian territories. "I want to assure you that we will support you as legitimate leader of the Palestinian people. I am sure you will do everything to restore unity," Putin told Palestinian President Abbas at the start of talks in the Kremlin. Abbas's visit to Moscow comes amid a crisis in the Palestinian territories. He fired his Hamas-led government last month after the faction forcibly took control of the Gaza Strip. Western states have sidelined Hamas since the takeover, focusing their aid and diplomatic efforts on Abbas's administration, with its headquarters in the West Bank. But Russia -- alone among members of the Quartet of Middle East peace brokers, which also include the United States, the United Nations and the European Union -- has maintained contacts with Hamas le
